Arista Networks, Inc. (NYSE:ANET) Downgraded to “Hold” at BidaskClub

					Posted by Danessa Lincoln on Jul 25th, 2017 // No Comments 




Arista Networks, Inc. (NYSE:ANET) was downgraded by research analysts at BidaskClub from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a note issued to investors on Tuesday.
ANET has been the topic of a number of other research reports. Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (The) raised Arista Networks from a “sell” rating to a “neutral” rating and lifted their target price for the company from $68.00 to $125.00 in a research report on Monday, March 27th. Gabelli  reaffirmed a “buy” rating on shares of Arista Networks in a research report on Sunday, April 2nd. Stifel Nicolaus lowered Arista Networks from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating and boosted their price target for the stock from $130.00 to $135.00 in a research report on Monday, April 3rd. They noted that the move was a valuation call. Needham & Company LLC  reaffirmed a “buy” rating and set a $150.00 price target on shares of Arista Networks in a research report on Thursday, April 6th. Finally, Wells Fargo & Company  reaffirmed an “outperform” rating on shares of Arista Networks in a research report on Thursday, April 6th. Seventeen research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating, fifteen have issued  a buy rating and one  has given a strong buy rating to the company. The company  has an average rating of “Buy” and a consensus target price of $140.00.


 Get Arista Networks Inc. alerts:



Arista Networks (NYSE:ANET) traded up 1.41% during midday trading on Tuesday, reaching $157.41. 183,662 shares of the company traded hands. The company has a 50-day moving average price of $153.57 and a 200-day moving average price of $131.11. Arista Networks has a 12-month low of $68.75 and a 12-month high of $162.97. The company has a market cap of $11.33 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 50.84 and a beta of 1.35. 




Arista Networks (NYSE:ANET) last announced its quarterly earnings data on Thursday, May 4th. The technology company reported $0.79 EPS for the quarter, topping the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.70 by $0.09. The firm had revenue of $335.48 million during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $326.19 million. Arista Networks had a return on equity of 20.94% and a net margin of 18.95%. The company’s revenue was up 38.5% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period last year, the company earned $0.68 earnings per share.  On average, analysts predict that  Arista Networks will post $3.96 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: “Arista Networks, Inc. (NYSE:ANET) Downgraded to “Hold” at BidaskClub” was  posted by Markets Daily and is the property of of Markets Daily. If you are reading this report on another site, it was stolen and republished in violation of international trademark and copyright legislation. The legal version of this report can be read at https://www.themarketsdaily.com/2017/07/25/arista-networks-inc-nyseanet-downgraded-to-hold-at-bidaskclub.html. 
In related news, insider Anshul Sadana sold 12,000 shares of Arista Networks stock in a transaction on Monday, July 17th. The stock was sold at an average price of $154.51, for a total transaction of $1,854,120.00. Following the completion of the sale, the insider now owns 99,841 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $15,426,432.91. The transaction was disclosed in a filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is available through this link. Also, insider Jayshree Ullal sold 22,763 shares of Arista Networks stock in a transaction on Wednesday, July 19th. The shares were sold at an average price of $157.81, for a total value of $3,592,229.03. Following the sale, the insider now directly owns 2,576 shares of the company’s stock, valued at approximately $406,518.56. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Insiders have sold 648,962 shares of company stock valued at $98,381,418 over the last ninety days. 28.09% of the stock is currently owned by company insiders. 
A number of large investors have recently bought and sold shares of ANET. Comerica Bank purchased a new stake in shares of  Arista Networks during the fourth quarter valued at about $205,000.  Norges Bank purchased a new stake in shares of  Arista Networks during the fourth quarter valued at about $31,517,000.  Deane Retirement Strategies Inc. raised its stake in shares of  Arista Networks by 5.6% in the first quarter. Deane Retirement Strategies Inc. now owns 59,153 shares of the technology company’s stock valued at $7,827,000 after buying an additional 3,135 shares during the period.  Creative Planning raised its stake in shares of  Arista Networks by 855.0% in the first quarter. Creative Planning now owns 11,880 shares of the technology company’s stock valued at $1,571,000 after buying an additional 10,636 shares during the period.  Finally, Bank of Montreal Can raised its stake in shares of  Arista Networks by 7,327.6% in the first quarter. Bank of Montreal Can now owns 22,357 shares of the technology company’s stock valued at $2,957,000 after buying an additional 22,056 shares during the period. 60.96% of the stock is owned by institutional investors. 
About Arista Networks
Arista Networks, Inc is a supplier of cloud networking solutions that use software innovations to address the needs of Internet companies, cloud service providers and data centers for enterprise support. It develops, markets and sells cloud networking solutions, which consist of its Gigabit Ethernet switches and related software.







